{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6dd2ee54-b893-4a63-b85c-da01d68d9943","content":"I've reviewed all the project files. Here are the **three evaluation performance anti-patterns** in this project:\n\n---\n\n### 1. 🐌 File I/O Property Function (line 13, `EvalHeavy.csproj`)\n```xml\n<BuildNotes>$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))</BuildNotes>\n```\n`System.IO.File::ReadAllText` performs **disk I/O during evaluation**, blocking the evaluation pipeline. This runs on every evaluation — IDE load, build, restore, etc.\n\n**Fix:** Move this to a target with `Inputs/Outputs` so it only runs during build when the file changes.\n\n---\n\n### 2. 🐌 Expensive Wildcard Glob (line 9, `EvalHeavy.csproj`)\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" Exclude=\"**\\bin\\**;**\\obj\\**\" />\n```\n`**\\*.*` walks the **entire directory tree** at evaluation time. This gets progressively worse as the repo grows (especially with `node_modules`, `.git`, large artifact dirs). Only `bin`/`obj` are excluded.\n\n**Fix:** Use `DefaultItemExcludes` to exclude heavy directories, or narrow the glob to specific extensions/subdirectories.\n\n---\n\n### 3. 🐌 Deep Import Chain (3 levels)\n```\nEvalHeavy.csproj → level1.props → level2.props → level3.props\n```\nEach import adds file-existence checks and XML parsing during evaluation. While 3 levels is moderate, this pattern doesn't scale — chains >20 levels cause measurable slowdowns. Flatten where possible.\n\n---\n\n**Impact priority:** The file I/O property function (#1) and broad glob (#2) are the most impactful. The import chain (#3) is low-severity here but worth watching as the project grows.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"32dfb0e4-1128-47e9-a765-cfa958377ad5","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I have a complete picture of the project. Let me analyze it for MSBuild evaluation performance issues. I can see several issues:\n\n1. **Deep import chain**: `EvalHeavy.csproj` → `level1.props` → `level2.props` → `level3.props` (3 levels deep). While 3 levels isn't terrible on its own, deep import chains add overhead to evaluation.\n\n2. **Expensive glob pattern**: `<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" Exclude=\"**\\bin\\**;**\\obj\\**\" />` — this uses a `**\\*.*` wildcard glob that walks the entire directory tree. This is a classic evaluation performance anti-pattern.\n\n\n3. **File I/O during evaluation**: There's a property function that reads from disk at evaluation time, which blocks the pipeline and is a significant bottleneck.\n\nLet me apply the eval-performance skill to address these issues.","outputTokens":707,"requestId":"1413:1605AB:61907AB:6D07555:69EC1685"},"id":"7998c1bb-f924-4b62-9231-fffd22581b22","timestamp":"2026-04-25T01:19:18.576Z","parentId":"d69e5a52-b692-4969-8929-8daaceca5c9d"}
